Bauchi State Governor, Bala Abdulkadir Mohammed has assured people of the state that he will work tirelessly to perform better than his predecessors. The Governor spoke while receiving officials of the State Council, Christian Association of Nigeria, who paid him a Christmas Homage. The Governor who was responding to the numerous challenges affecting the economy of the state said his administration was committed to leaving landmark legacies. He reassured people of the state that his administration will give them equal opportunity without religious or political consideration. On the celebration of this year’s Christmas, the governor called on the Christian community in the state to use the occasion for sober reflection. Governor Bala Mohammed used the medium to expressed gratitude to them for their massive support during the conduct of the last gubernatorial election in the state. Earlier, the State Chairman, Christian Association of Nigeria, Reverend Joshua Ray Maina assured the governor of their total support through prayers for the success of his administration. Reverend Joshua Maina applauded the governor for sponsoring 110 Christians to participate in the 2019 pilgrimage. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.